org.overture.interpreter.values

Class TransactionValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.overture.interpreter.values.Value
      • org.overture.interpreter.values.ReferenceValue
        • org.overture.interpreter.values.UpdatableValue
          • org.overture.interpreter.values.TransactionValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<Value>, Formattable

    public class TransactionValue
extends UpdatableValue
    A class to hold an updatable value that can be modified by VDM-RT threads in transactions, committed at a duration point.

      • getUpdatable

        public Value getUpdatable(ValueListenerList watch)
        Description copied from class: Value
        Return an UpdatableValue, wrapping this one. This is a deep translation that recurses into all Values that contain other Values (sets etc), converting their contents to UpdateableValues. The results can then be modified in assignment statements or used as state data etc.
        Overrides:
        getUpdatable in class UpdatableValue
        Parameters:
        watch - The listener to inform of updates to the value.
        Returns:
        An UpdatableValue for this one.

        Change the object's value. Normally, values are immutable, but subclasses of UpdatableValue implement this set method to replace the object referenced with another. ReferenceValues like UpdatableValue delegate all the other Value method to the contained object.

      • deref

        public Value deref()
        Description copied from class: Value
        Find the most primitive underlying value contained. This is typically used to check whether a value is "really" (say) a MapValue once the ReferenceValue (Updatablevalue) wrappers have been removed. Note that this strips InvariantTypes of their invariance!
        Overrides:
        deref in class UpdatableValue
        Returns:
        The primitive value

      • getConstant

        public Value getConstant()
        Description copied from class: Value
        Return a simple Value, removing any Updatable/TransactionValue wrappers. This is the opposite of getUpdatable(), though it works for all values. Note that this will preserve InvariantValues' integrity (unlike deref).
        Overrides:
        getConstant in class UpdatableValue
        Returns:
        A simple value
